171
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:50,151
What was Father Flynn's sermon about?

172
00:16:52,077 --> 00:16:56,707
Well, doubt.
He was talking about doubt.

173
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:02,244
Why?
- Excuse me, Sister?

174
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:05,491
Well, sermons come from somewhere,
don't they?

175
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:07,821
Is Father Flynn in doubt?

176
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:11,785
Is he concerned
that someone else is in doubt?

177
00:17:12,097 --> 00:17:13,699
I suppose you'd have to ask him.

178
00:17:13,799 --> 00:17:15,901
No, that would not be appropriate.

179
00:17:16,001 --> 00:17:17,503
He is my superior,

180
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:20,439
and if he were troubled
he should confess it to a fellow priest...

181
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,241
...or to the monsignor.

182
00:17:22,341 --> 00:17:24,944
We do not share
intimate information with priests.

183
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,044
No.
- That's true.

184
00:17:30,115 --> 00:17:32,115
What are we saying?

185
00:17:32,785 --> 00:17:35,276
I want you all to be alert.

186
