00:22:26,478 --> 00:22:29,815
The students are not using them
for assignments, I hope.

249
00:22:29,915 --> 00:22:30,983
No, of course not.

250
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:34,319
I am sorry I allowed even
cartridge pens into this school.

251
00:22:34,419 --> 00:22:36,855
Always easy way out, these days.

252
00:22:36,955 --> 00:22:38,123
(ALO YSIUS SIGHS)

253
00:22:38,223 --> 00:22:42,327
Every easy choice today
will have its consequence tomorrow.

254
00:22:42,427 --> 00:22:44,363
Mark my words.
- Yes, Sister.

255
00:22:44,463 --> 00:22:46,365
Ballpoints make them press down.

256
00:22:46,465 --> 00:22:48,333
When they press down,
they write like monkeys.

257
00:22:48,433 --> 00:22:53,193
I don't allow them ballpoint pens.
- And yet here one is.

258
00:22:54,272 --> 00:22:58,208
Penmanship is dying
all across this country.

259
00:22:59,010 --> 00:23:01,010
I hope not.

260
00:23:01,947 --> 00:23:04,415
You should frame something.

261
00:23:04,516 --> 00:23:08,782
Put it up on the blackboard.
Put the pope up.

262
00:23:09,921 --> 00:23:12,324
That's the wrong pope. He's deceased.

263
00:23:12,424 --> 00:23:17,195
I don't care what pope it is.
Use the glass to see behind you.

264
00:23:17,295 --> 00:23:21,400
Children should think you have eyes
in the back of your head.

265
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,435
Wouldn't that be a little frightening?

266
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:26,471
Only to the ones who are up to no good.

267
00:23:26,571 --> 00:23:28,571
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

268
00:23:33,278 --> 00:23:35,828
FLYNN: Relax. Put it up there.

269
00:23:37,783 --> 00:23:39,783
All right, now.

270
00:23:40,719 --> 00:23:44,589
The thing about shooting
from the foul line is it's psychological.

271
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:47,459
All right, come up with a routine.

272
00:23:47,559 --> 00:23:50,395
You shift your weight, move your hips...

273
00:23:50,495 --> 00:23:51,530
...(BOYS LAUGHING)

274
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:52,898
Yeah, you think that's funny, Ralph?

275
00:23:52,998 --> 00:23:54,633
You know what's funny is
you never getting a foul shot.

276
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,901
(BOYS LAUGHING)

277
00:23:56,001 --> 00:24:02,206
All right, concentrate on the routine,
and you'll forget to get tensed up.

278
00:24:03,542 --> 00:24:05,837
All right, go ahead, Jimmy.

279
00:24:08,980 --> 00:24:09,981
(SWISHING)

280
00:24:10,081 --> 00:24:15,861
Good man. You listen. That's good.
All right, now sit down, everyone.

281
00:24:16,688 --> 00:24:18,688
Good.

282
00:24:18,757 --> 00:24:24,452
On another matter, I've noticed
several of you guys got dirty nails.

283
00:24:25,764 --> 00:24:27,933
All right, I don't want to see that.

284
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:29,601
I'm not talking about
the length of your nails.

285
00:24:29,701 --> 00:24:32,137
I'm talking about cleanliness.

286
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:34,237
See, look at my nails.

287
00:24:38,243 --> 00:24:40,878
All right, they're long.
- Whoa.

288
00:24:41,246 --> 00:24:47,082
Yeah, I like them a little long,
but look at how clean they are.

289
00:24:56,895 --> 00:24:58,895
That makes it okay.

290
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:06,765
FLYNN: The climpity-clomp.
Clomp-clomp-clomp.

291
00:25:06,905 --> 00:25:09,625
Harder than a herd of elephants.

292
00:25:13,945 --> 00:25:15,781
You are wicked.

293
00:25:15,881 --> 00:25:17,816
No, I told her, 'You're her mother.

294
00:25:17,916 --> 00:25:21,686
'You raised her. You fed her.
You tell her she's fat.'

295
00:25:21,786 --> 00:25:23,789
But wait, how fat is she?

296
00:25:23,889 --> 00:25:26,525
What, the mother or the daughter?
- The daughter.

297
00:25:26,625 --> 00:25:27,893
I never met the daughter.

298
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:30,373
What about the mother?
- Fat.

299
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:49,212
(BELLS JINGLING)...

300
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:57,670
...(FLYNN PRAYING IN LATIN)...

301
00:26:22,213 --> 00:26:24,213
...(BELL TOLLING)

302
00:26:24,282 --> 00:26:27,085
Father, we having practice after school?

303
00:26:27,185 --> 00:26:31,265
If you guys want it, we can have it.
Let me know.

304
00:26:32,324 --> 00:26:36,561
JAMES: The Fascist governments
of Germany and Italy...

305
00:26:36,661 --> 00:26:39,466
...were already working together.

306
00:26:39,698 --> 00:26:42,248
They formed the Pact of Steel.

307
00:26:43,068 --> 00:26:44,536
The Pact of Steel was...

308
00:26:44,636 --> 00:26:45,770
Hi.
- Hi.

309
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:50,709
...a military alliance between
Benito Mussolini and Adolf Hitler.

310
00:26:50,809 --> 00:26:56,844
Mr. London, get back in your seat
and stop bothering Miss Horan, please.

311
00:26:58,984 --> 00:27:00,252
Now, who can tell me...

312
00:27:00,352 --> 00:27:02,352
...(PHONE BUZZING)

313
00:27:04,689 --> 00:27:06,689
Yes?

314
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:09,025
Yes. Of course, Father.

315
00:27:11,196 --> 00:27:14,341
Donald? You should go to the rectory.

316
00:27:17,802 --> 00:27:19,471
(BLAME IT ON
THE BOSSA NO VA PLAYING)

317
00:27:19,571 --> 00:27:25,407
Two, three, four, five, six, seven,
eight, nine, ten, eleven.

318
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:31,710
Go one, two, three, touch.
One, two, three, kick.

319
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:37,015
And back, side, front, kick.
Back, side, front. Again.

320
00:27:37,155 --> 00:27:39,620
(SIN GIN G) We began to dance

321
00:27:39,724 --> 00:27:41,919
Swaying to and fro

322
00:27:43,361 --> 00:27:47,127
And soon I knew I'd never let him go...

323
00:27:48,066 --> 00:27:50,969
Raymond, what are you doing?
- The mashed potato.

324
00:27:51,069 --> 00:27:53,238
You're supposed to be doing
the bossa nova.

325
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:57,163
But I know the mashed potato.
- (LAUGHS) Oh...

326
00:27:58,376 --> 00:28:03,148
MRS. SHIELDS: All right, now follow.
Back, side, front, kick.

327
00:28:03,248 --> 00:28:08,151
Back, side... One, two, three, kick.

328
00:28:08,253 --> 00:28:13,088
Back, side, front, kick.
Back, side, front...

329
00:28:14,259 --> 00:28:15,293
...(LOCKER DOOR OPENING)

330
00:28:15,393 --> 00:28:19,798
Let me get in front of you
so that you can see what I'm doing.

331
00:28:19,898 --> 00:28:22,696
And one, two, three, touch.

332
00:28:22,801 --> 00:28:25,861
One, two, three, kick.

333
00:28:25,970 --> 00:28:30,873
Back, side, front, kick.
Back, side, front...

334
00:28:31,943 --> 00:28:36,505
Okay. This is really good.
Very good there.

335
00:28:36,614 --> 00:28:38,416
Now I'm glad to say

336
00:28:38,516 --> 00:28:40,516
I'm his bride to be

337
00:28:41,753 --> 00:28:46,656
And we're gonna raise a family...

338
00:29:07,312 --> 00:29:09,610
...(STUDENTS CHATTERING)...

339
00:29:17,822 --> 00:29:21,222
JAMES: Donald, are you feeling ill?
- No.

340
00:29:21,993 --> 00:29:24,655
Are you sure?
- Yes.

341
00:29:26,464 --> 00:29:31,128
Are you all right?
- I just want to go home.

342
00:29:52,056 --> 00:29:56,261
Good afternoon, Sister.
- Good afternoon, Sister James.

343
00:29:56,361 --> 00:30:00,441
Sister, can I speak with you
about Donald Miller?

344
00:30:02,500 --> 00:30:05,870
ALO YSIUS: Is he being accepted?
JAMES: He has no friends.

345
00:30:05,970 --> 00:30:11,240
ALO YSIUS: That would be a lot
to expect after only two months.

346
00:30:11,342 --> 00:30:14,038
Has anyone hit him?
- No.

347
00:30:15,413 --> 00:30:17,540
Someone will.

348
00:30:17,682 --> 00:30:23,678
And when that happens,
send them right down to me.

349
00:30:25,356 --> 00:30:27,736
I'm not so sure anyone will.

350
00:30:29,227 --> 00:30:32,163
This parish serves Irish and Italian families.

351
00:30:32,263 --> 00:30:34,898
Someone will hit Donald Miller.

352
00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:38,201
He has a protector.

353
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:40,670
Who?

354
00:30:45,877 --> 00:30:47,877
Father Flynn.

355
00:30:53,885 --> 00:30:55,885
What?

356
00:30:58,923 --> 00:31:00,923
He's taken an interest.

357
00:31:18,209 --> 00:31:22,714
I told you to come to me,
but I hoped you never would.

358
00:31:23,147 --> 00:31:24,415
Maybe I shouldn't have.

359
00:31:24,515 --> 00:31:26,515
(SIGHING)

360
00:31:27,418 --> 00:31:29,418
So, it's happened.

361
00:31:30,989 --> 00:31:36,327
What? Oh, no. I'm not telling you that.
I'm not even certain what you mean.

362
00:31:36,427 --> 00:31:38,229
Oh, excuse me there, Sisters.

363
00:31:38,329 --> 00:31:41,729
No bother. We're done here.
Come, Sister.

364
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:54,110
What have you seen?

365
00:31:55,513 --> 00:31:57,515
It is unsettling
to look at people with suspicion.

366
00:31:57,615 --> 00:31:59,217
I feel less close to God.

367
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:01,452
When you take a step
to address wrongdoing,

368
00:32:01,552 --> 00:32:06,227
you are taking a step away from God,
but in his service.

369
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:08,591
What have you seen?

370
00:32:10,929 --> 00:32:12,163
Good afternoon, Sisters.

371
00:32:12,263 --> 00:32:14,999
Good afternoon, Mrs. Carson.
Why the cat?

372
00:32:15,099 --> 00:32:18,244
'Cause there's a mouse.
Want some tea?

373
00:32:18,269 --> 00:32:20,705
If you don't want to dance with her,
don't dance with her.

374
00:32:20,805 --> 00:32:22,805
Well, is it wrong?
- No.

375
00:32:24,475 --> 00:32:26,511
But what if the girl turns you down?

376
00:32:26,611 --> 00:32:28,611
(BOYS LAUGHING)

377
00:32:28,646 --> 00:32:31,749
All right, you have the right
to ask a girl to dance.

378
00:32:31,849 --> 00:32:34,586
All right,
she has the right to turn you down.

379
00:32:34,686 --> 00:32:38,122
The trick is, don't take it to heart.

380
00:32:38,256 --> 00:32:40,891
What if they all turn you down?

381
00:32:41,492 --> 00:32:43,061
Well, then you become a priest.

382
00:32:43,161 --> 00:32:45,161
(BOYS LAUGHING)...

383
00:32:45,730 --> 00:32:47,730
...(FLYNN CHUCKLING)

384
00:32:49,667 --> 00:32:51,792
All right, next question.

385
00:33:00,712 --> 00:33:02,712
What have you seen?

386
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:10,188
He called Donald Miller to the rectory.

387
00:33:10,288 --> 00:33:11,956
What for?
- A talk.

388
00:33:12,056 --> 00:33:13,124
Alone?
- Yes.

389
00:33:13,224 --> 00:33:16,193
When?
- A week ago during class.

390
00:33:16,327 --> 00:33:17,929
Why didn't you tell me?

391
00:33:18,029 --> 00:33:22,024
I didn't think
there was anything wrong with it.

392
00:33:26,971 --> 00:33:29,946
Of all the children, Donald Miller.

393
00:33:31,376 --> 00:33:32,744
I suppose it makes sense.

394
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:35,980
How does it make sense?
- He's isolated.

395
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:41,350
I don't know that anything is wrong.
- Our first Negro student.

396
00:33:41,486 --> 00:33:45,481
I thought there would be fighting.
Thought we...

397
00:33:46,224 --> 00:33:48,689
A parent or two to deal with.

398
00:33:51,429 --> 00:33:54,829
I should have foreseen this possibility.

399
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:56,567
How could you imagine it?

400
00:33:56,667 --> 00:34:01,002
Well, it's my job
to outshine the fox in cleverness.

401
00:34:04,909 --> 00:34:08,309
That is my job.
- But maybe it's nothing.

402
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:11,180
(ALO YSIUS SIGHING)

403
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:16,045
Then why do you look like
you've seen the devil?

404
00:34:20,091 --> 00:34:22,360
It's just the way the boy acted
when he came back to class.

405
00:34:22,460 --> 00:34:24,462
He said something?
- No, it was his expression.

406
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:26,431
He looked frightened.

407
00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:31,886
And he put his head on the desk
in the most peculiar way, and...

408
00:34:33,137 --> 00:34:38,237
And one other thing,
I think there was alcohol on his breath.

409
00:34:43,448 --> 00:34:47,407
There was alcohol on his breath.

410
00:34:56,561 --> 00:34:58,561
(JAMES SNIFFLING)...

411
00:34:58,996 --> 00:35:00,996
...(PATTING)

412
00:35:03,601 --> 00:35:07,511
Years ago at Saint Boniface
there was a priest.

413
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:16,073
But I had Father Scully then.

414
00:35:19,951 --> 00:35:24,371
Here, there's no man I can go to.
Men run everything.

415
00:35:24,489 --> 00:35:28,059
We are going to have to
stop him ourselves.

416
00:35:30,261 --> 00:35:33,491
There we go. She got him. Takes a cat.

417
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:37,907
ALO YSIUS: Yes, it does.

418
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:46,142
Yes, it does.

419
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:51,480
(ALL CHATTERING)...

420
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,320
...(RAINING HEAVILY)

421
00:36:27,385 --> 00:36:29,153
This towel will never be dead white again.

422
00:36:29,253 --> 00:36:30,621
Yes, it will.

423
00:36:30,721 --> 00:36:33,591
RAYMOND: Mrs. Carson.
VERONICA: I'm fine.

424
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:36,294
What happened?
- There's a branch down.

425
00:36:36,394 --> 00:36:38,262
Are you all right, Sister?
- RAYMOND: She didn't see it.

426
00:36:38,362 --> 00:36:42,458
Fine. Just bushwhacked.
No need for a fuss.

427
00:36:42,567 --> 00:36:44,502
You just go lie down.
I'll bring you some tea.

428
00:36:44,602 --> 00:36:46,437
MRS. CARSON: Come with me.
VERONICA: I just...

429
00:36:46,537 --> 00:36:50,007
RAYMOND: I'll get you a compress.
- I did not fail to see it.

430
00:36:50,107 --> 00:36:52,143
MR. McGUINN: Hello? Yes, Sister.
- Mr. McGuinn.

431
00:36:52,243 --> 00:36:55,279
Could you look in on the courtyard?
I've got branches falling.

432
00:36:55,379 --> 00:36:57,506
What has?
- A branch has.

433
00:37:01,886 --> 00:37:06,755
Watch your step here, Sister.
I'll cut it up.

434
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:11,595
The world is crashing, Michael.

435
00:37:11,596 --> 00:37:14,932
I haven't heard a wind like that
since I left Mullingar.

436
00:37:15,032 --> 00:37:19,537
I've never known a wind like it.
The wind has changed.

437
00:37:34,652 --> 00:37:36,652
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

438
00:37:41,726 --> 00:37:44,786
What are you doing out here, Conroy?

439
00:37:45,329 --> 00:37:47,539
I talked in class, Father.

440
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:51,094
(FLYNN SIGHING)

441
00:37:59,610 --> 00:38:01,990
Waiting for Sister Aloysius.

442
00:38:05,416 --> 00:38:08,579
She know you're here?
- She knows.

443
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:14,192
Good morning, Father Flynn.
Good of you to come by.

444
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:16,227
Morning, Sister Aloysius.
How are you today?

445
00:38:16,327 --> 00:38:17,495
I'm very well, thank you.

446
00:38:17,595 --> 00:38:19,720
Mr. Conroy.
- Yes, Sister.

447
00:38:19,797 --> 00:38:21,797
Mr. Transistor Radio.

448
00:38:21,799 --> 00:38:23,267
(SIGHS)

449
00:38:23,367 --> 00:38:25,603
Multiplication table, 10 times,
in its totality,

450
00:38:25,703 --> 00:38:27,538
delivered to me tomorrow morning.

451
00:38:27,638 --> 00:38:28,940
Legible, boy.

452
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,374
(SIGHS)

453
00:38:30,474 --> 00:38:34,069
Return to class. Go. Go, go.

454
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:49,209
I'd invite you in,
but we're just short Sister James.

455
00:38:54,965 --> 00:38:58,705
Hear that wind last night?
- I certainly did.

456
00:39:00,871 --> 00:39:02,073
Oh.

457
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:03,941
Did I hear Sister Veronica had an accident?

458
00:39:04,041 --> 00:39:07,612
Yeah. Sister Veronica fell,
practically killed herself.

459
00:39:07,712 --> 00:39:10,602
Is she all right?
- Oh, she's fine.

460
00:39:12,883 --> 00:39:18,748
Her sight isn't good, is it?
- Her sight is fine. Nuns fall, you know.

461
00:39:19,323 --> 00:39:20,491
Nah, I didn't know that.

462
00:39:20,591 --> 00:39:24,128
It's the habit.
It catches us up more often than not.

463
00:39:24,228 --> 00:39:25,196
(CHUCKLES)

464
00:39:25,296 --> 00:39:26,297
FLYNN: Hmm.

465
00:39:26,397 --> 00:39:28,522
We go down like dominoes.

466
00:39:29,767 --> 00:39:32,236
Am I past the time?
- Not at all.

467
00:39:32,336 --> 00:39:33,904
Good morning, Father.
Good morning, Sister.

468
00:39:34,004 --> 00:39:36,131
I'm sorry I was delayed.

469
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:38,976
I ran into Sister Veronica.
- How is she?

470
00:39:39,076 --> 00:39:41,812
I'm afraid she has a bit of a bloody nose.

471
00:39:41,912 --> 00:39:45,737
I'm beginning to think
you're punching people.

472
00:39:46,517 --> 00:39:47,785
Sister?

473
00:39:47,885 --> 00:39:50,683
First, William London and now...

474
00:39:53,023 --> 00:39:57,892
Never mind. Well, come in, please.
- Sister.

475
00:40:00,097 --> 00:40:03,931
Please. Sit. Have a seat.

476
00:40:04,068 --> 00:40:05,836
I actually have a hot pot of tea.

477
00:40:05,936 --> 00:40:09,997
And close this,
but not quite for form's sake.

478
00:40:10,875 --> 00:40:13,510
Father, would you care for a...

479
00:40:15,312 --> 00:40:19,383
Would you have a cup of tea, Father?
- I'd love a cup of tea.

480
00:40:19,483 --> 00:40:22,153
Sister, perhaps you could serve him.
- I'd be glad.

481
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:23,554
And yourself, of course.

482
00:40:23,654 --> 00:40:24,855
Would you like a cup of tea,
Sister Aloysius?

483
00:40:24,955 --> 00:40:26,691
No, I've already had my cup.

484
00:40:26,791 --> 00:40:30,249
Is there sugar?
- Sugar?

485
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:38,926
Yes, yes. Somewhere here.

486
00:40:40,638 --> 00:40:44,909
I put it in the drawer for Lent last year.
Never remembered to take it out.

487
00:40:45,009 --> 00:40:46,977
It mustn't have been much to give up, then.

488
00:40:47,077 --> 00:40:48,446
(ALO YSIUS CHUCKLES)...

489
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:49,547
...(FLYNN CHUCKLES)

490
00:40:49,647 --> 00:40:52,550
ALO YSIUS: I'm sure you're right.
Here it is.

491
00:40:52,650 --> 00:40:59,249
I'll serve you, although
for want of practice I'm a little clumsy.

492
00:41:01,158 --> 00:41:05,959
I see your fingernails.
- Wear them a little long.

493
00:41:07,665 --> 00:41:09,367
The sugar?
- Yes. One?

494
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:11,467
Three.

495
00:41:11,669 --> 00:41:13,669
Three?
- Sweet tooth.

496
00:41:14,104 --> 00:41:17,096
Two. Three.

497
00:41:18,209 --> 00:41:21,303
Sister, you care for sugar?
- Never.

498
00:41:21,445 --> 00:41:25,100
Not that there's anything wrong with sugar.

499
00:41:25,850 --> 00:41:28,686
Well, thank you, Father,
for making time for us.

500
00:41:28,786 --> 00:41:30,454
We are at our wit's end.

501
00:41:30,554 --> 00:41:34,692
I think it's an excellent idea
to rethink the Christmas pageant,

502
00:41:34,792 --> 00:41:37,895
'cause last year's effort
was a little woebegone.

503
00:41:37,995 --> 00:41:41,866
Oh, I loved it, but I love all pageants.
The hymns.

504
00:41:41,966 --> 00:41:45,369
O Little Town of Bethlehem, O Come,
O Come, Emmanuel, O Come...

505
00:41:45,469 --> 00:41:47,772
ALO YSIUS: All right.
Thank you, Sister James.

506
00:41:47,872 --> 00:41:48,939
So what do you think, Father?

507
00:41:49,039 --> 00:41:51,409
(CLEARS THROAT)
Is there something new we could do?

508
00:41:51,509 --> 00:41:53,978
Well, we all love the Christmas hymns,

509
00:41:54,078 --> 00:41:58,073
but it might be jolly
to include a secular song.

510
00:41:58,315 --> 00:42:00,117
Secular?
- Yes.

511
00:42:00,217 --> 00:42:03,320
It's Beginning To Look A Lot
Like Christmas. Something like that.

512
00:42:03,420 --> 00:42:06,990
What would be the point of a secular song?

513
00:42:07,091 --> 00:42:08,292
Just fun.

514
00:42:08,392 --> 00:42:10,494
Or Frosty the Snowman.
- FLYNN: That's a good one.

515
00:42:10,594 --> 00:42:15,599
We could have one of the boys
dress up as a snowman, dance around.

516
00:42:15,699 --> 00:42:17,699
Which boy?

517
00:42:21,071 --> 00:42:22,606
We'd do tryouts.

518
00:42:22,706 --> 00:42:27,234
Frosty the Snowman
espouses a pagan belief in magic.

519
00:42:27,378 --> 00:42:31,348
The snowman comes to life when
an enchanted hat is put on his head.

520
00:42:31,448 --> 00:42:32,950
If the music were more somber,

521
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:38,189
people would realize the images
are disturbing and the song heretical.

522
00:42:38,289 --> 00:42:41,659
I never thought about
Frosty the Snowman like that.

523
00:42:41,759 --> 00:42:42,927
It should be banned from the airwaves.

524
00:42:43,027 --> 00:42:45,322
So, not Frosty the Snowman.

525
00:42:45,329 --> 00:42:51,268
Oh, It's Beginning To Look A Lot Like
Christmas would be fine, I suppose.

526
00:42:51,368 --> 00:42:53,368
Parents would like it.

527
00:42:55,205 --> 00:42:59,543
May I ask what you're writing down
with that ballpoint pen?

528
00:42:59,643 --> 00:43:03,010
Oh, nothing. It's an idea for a sermon.

529
00:43:03,447 --> 00:43:07,384
Oh. You had one right now?
- I get them all the time.

530
00:43:07,484 --> 00:43:08,986
How fortunate.

531
00:43:09,086 --> 00:43:11,455
I forget them,
so I have to write them down.

532
00:43:11,555 --> 00:43:12,990
Oh.

533
00:43:13,090 --> 00:43:15,090
What is the idea?

534
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:18,927
Intolerance.

535
00:43:24,301 --> 00:43:25,703
Would you like a little more tea, Father?

536
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:27,803
Not yet.

537
00:43:28,939 --> 00:43:30,979
It's a new time, Sister.

538
00:43:31,075 --> 00:43:34,245
What's new about it?
- Something inside of people is new.

539
00:43:34,345 --> 00:43:37,320
There is nothing new under the sun.

540
00:43:40,084 --> 00:43:42,379
The Church needs to change.

541
00:43:43,153 --> 00:43:46,090
We should sing a song
from the radio now and then,

542
00:43:46,190 --> 00:43:47,892
take the kids out for ice cream.

543
00:43:47,992 --> 00:43:49,193
Sweet tooth.

544
00:43:49,293 --> 00:43:52,263
And maybe take the boys
on a camping trip.

545
00:43:52,363 --> 00:43:54,363
The point being?

546
00:43:55,332 --> 00:43:57,372
We should be friendlier.

547
00:43:58,002 --> 00:43:59,937
You know, the children and the parents...

548
00:44:00,037 --> 00:44:02,273
...should see us as members of their family.

549
00:44:02,373 --> 00:44:07,106
But we are not members of their family.
We're different.

550
00:44:07,778 --> 00:44:12,181
Why? Because of our vows?
- Precisely.

551
00:44:13,617 --> 00:44:15,920
I don't think we're so different.

552
00:44:16,020 --> 00:44:17,755
You know, Sister,
I would take some more tea.

553
00:44:17,855 --> 00:44:21,000
And they think we're different, yeah?

554
00:44:21,025 --> 00:44:22,626
The working...

555
00:44:22,726 --> 00:44:28,187
The working class people of this parish
trust us to be different.

556
00:44:28,332 --> 00:44:29,800
I think we're getting off the subject.

557
00:44:29,900 --> 00:44:31,569
Yes, you're right. You're right.
You're right. Back to it.

558
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:33,669
(PHONE BUZZING)

559
00:44:38,876 --> 00:44:40,210
Yes?

560
00:44:40,310 --> 00:44:42,437
Sister Raymond? Mmm.

561
00:44:44,181 --> 00:44:48,218
Well, you tell her to wash her face
and her neck and report to me at 3:00.

562
00:44:48,318 --> 00:44:50,318
Yeah.

563
00:44:51,288 --> 00:44:54,689
Excuse me. The Christmas pageant.

564
00:44:55,793 --> 00:44:57,828
(CLEARS THROAT) We must be careful...

565
00:44:57,928 --> 00:44:59,430
...how Donald Miller is used in the pageant.

566
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:02,693
Easy there, Sister.
- Father.

567
00:45:08,472 --> 00:45:10,307
All right, what about Donald Miller?

568
00:45:10,407 --> 00:45:12,610
We must be careful, in the pageant,

569
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:17,300
that we neither hide Donald Miller
nor put him forward.

570
00:45:20,084 --> 00:45:23,420
Because of the color of his skin?
- That's right, yeah.

571
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:27,047
Why?
- Oh, come, Father.

572
00:45:27,191 --> 00:45:31,356
I think he should be treated
like every other boy.

573
00:45:31,562 --> 00:45:36,662
Well, you yourself singled the boy out
for special attention.

574
00:45:38,235 --> 00:45:43,730
You held a private meeting with him
at the rectory. A week ago?

575
00:45:43,874 --> 00:45:45,874
Yes.

576
00:45:48,879 --> 00:45:52,474
What are we talking about?
- Donald Miller.

577
00:45:56,720 --> 00:46:00,885
The boy acted strangely
when he returned to class.

578
00:46:01,725 --> 00:46:02,926
He did?

579
00:46:03,026 --> 00:46:07,097
When he returned from the rectory,
a little odd, yes.

580
00:46:07,197 --> 00:46:09,197
Can you tell us why?

581
00:46:11,235 --> 00:46:13,360
How did he act strangely?

582
00:46:14,037 --> 00:46:16,037
He...

583
00:46:16,306 --> 00:46:21,916
I'm not sure how to explain it.
He laid his head on the desk and...

584
00:46:25,315 --> 00:46:26,784
Do you mean you had some impression?

585
00:46:26,884 --> 00:46:27,951
Yes.

586
00:46:28,051 --> 00:46:30,521
And he'd come from the rectory,
so you're asking me?

587
00:46:30,621 --> 00:46:32,621
Mmm. That's it.

588
00:46:32,723 --> 00:46:33,957
FLYNN: Hmm.

589
00:46:34,057 --> 00:46:35,826
ALO YSIUS: Mmm.

590
00:46:35,926 --> 00:46:36,894
Mmm.

591
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:38,495
(CLEARING THROAT)

592
00:46:38,595 --> 00:46:40,531
Did you want to discuss the pageant?
Is that why I'm here?

593
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:43,233
Or is this what you wanted to discuss?

594
00:46:43,333 --> 00:46:45,333
This.

595
00:46:46,069 --> 00:46:48,970
Well, I'm a little uncomfortable.

596
00:46:49,106 --> 00:46:51,996
ALO YSIUS: Why?
- Why do you think?

597
00:46:52,009 --> 00:46:54,311
The boy's well-being is my responsibility.

598
00:46:54,411 --> 00:46:56,180
(PHONE RINGING)

599
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:57,748
His well-being is not at issue.

600
00:46:57,848 --> 00:47:01,218
ALO YSIUS: I'm not satisfied
that that is true.

601
00:47:01,318 --> 00:47:04,633
He was upset when he returned to class.

602
00:47:05,155 --> 00:47:07,365
Did he say something?
- No.

603
00:47:09,393 --> 00:47:11,028
What happened in the rectory?

604
00:47:11,128 --> 00:47:12,396
(RINGING CONTINUES)

605
00:47:12,496 --> 00:47:13,664
Happened?

606
00:47:13,764 --> 00:47:14,832
Mmm.

607
00:47:14,932 --> 00:47:16,533
Nothing happened.
I had a talk with the boy.

608
00:47:16,633 --> 00:47:19,101
What about?
- Private matter.

609
00:47:19,203 --> 00:47:22,306
He's 12 years old.
What could be private?

610
00:47:22,406 --> 00:47:24,406
(RINGING CONTINUES)...

611
00:47:24,708 --> 00:47:27,343
Should I get...
- ALO YSIUS: No.

612
00:47:28,011 --> 00:47:30,011
I object to your tone.

613
00:47:30,614 --> 00:47:36,575
This is not about my tone
or your tone, Father Flynn.

614
00:47:39,223 --> 00:47:42,292
It's about arriving at the truth.
- Of what?

615
00:47:42,392 --> 00:47:48,262
You know what I'm talking about,
don't you? Hmm?

616
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:53,137
And you're controlling the expression
on your face right now, aren't you?

617
00:47:53,237 --> 00:47:55,237
My face?

618
00:47:57,207 --> 00:47:58,776
What exactly are you accusing me of?

619
00:47:58,876 --> 00:48:01,478
I'm not accusing you of anything,
Father Flynn.

620
00:48:01,578 --> 00:48:07,175
I am asking you to tell me
what happened in the rectory.

621
00:48:13,757 --> 00:48:16,307
I don't wish to continue this.

622
00:48:17,227 --> 00:48:18,562
And if you're dissatisfied with that,

623
00:48:18,662 --> 00:48:22,232
I suggest you speak to Monsignor Benedict.

624
00:48:22,532 --> 00:48:28,272
I can only imagine this unfortunate
behavior is the result of overwork.

625
00:48:28,372 --> 00:48:31,432
Have a good morning, Sister. Sister.

626
00:48:36,380 --> 00:48:40,749
There was alcohol on his breath...

627
00:48:42,753 --> 00:48:46,578
...when he returned
from his meeting with you.

628
00:48:49,693 --> 00:48:51,693
Alcohol?

629
00:48:52,863 --> 00:48:55,328
I did smell it on his breath.

630
00:49:00,704 --> 00:49:02,704
Well?

631
00:49:06,143 --> 00:49:08,143
Let this alone.
- No.

632
00:49:08,178 --> 00:49:10,218
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)...

633
00:49:12,349 --> 00:49:14,389
...(STUDENTS CHATTERING)

634
00:49:17,654 --> 00:49:22,074
Take your time, Father.
Would you like some more tea?

635
00:49:22,559 --> 00:49:24,854
You should've let it alone.

636
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:28,630
Not possible.

637
00:49:36,340 --> 00:49:40,165
Mr. McGuinn caught Donald
drinking altar wine.

638
00:49:41,311 --> 00:49:46,806
When I found out, I sent for him.
There were tears,

639
00:49:48,118 --> 00:49:53,924
and he begged not to be removed
from the altar boys. I took pity on him.

640
00:49:54,024 --> 00:49:57,361
I told him if no one else found out,
I'd let him stay on.

641
00:49:57,461 --> 00:50:01,265
What a relief. That explains everything.
Thanks be to God.

642
00:50:01,365 --> 00:50:04,340
Look, Sister, it was all a mistake.

643
00:50:08,872 --> 00:50:10,774
And if I talk to Mr. McGuinn?

644
00:50:10,874 --> 00:50:13,084
Talk to him, by all means.

645
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:14,278
But now that the boy's secret's out,

646
00:50:14,378 --> 00:50:16,113
I'm gonna have to remove him
from the altar boys.

647
00:50:16,213 --> 00:50:17,681
That's what I was trying to avoid.

648
00:50:17,781 --> 00:50:19,216
JAMES: You were trying to protect the boy.

649
00:50:19,316 --> 00:50:21,316
That's right.

650
00:50:21,451 --> 00:50:23,854
I might have done the same thing.

651
00:50:23,954 --> 00:50:26,556
Is there a way Donald could stay
on the altar boys?

652
00:50:26,656 --> 00:50:30,694
If the boy drank altar wine,
he can't continue as an altar boy.

653
00:50:30,794 --> 00:50:32,794
Of course.

654
00:50:34,631 --> 00:50:36,631
Are you satisfied?

655
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,000
Yes.

656
00:50:41,138 --> 00:50:43,138
Hmm.

657
00:50:43,306 --> 00:50:47,216
Well, I'll be going.
I have some writing to do.

658
00:50:47,310 --> 00:50:50,540
ALO YSIUS: Intolerance.
- That's right.

659
00:50:52,082 --> 00:50:55,652
I'm not pleased with how you handled this.

660
00:50:55,919 --> 00:50:57,919
Sister. Sister.

661
00:51:06,530 --> 00:51:08,530
Well...

662
00:51:09,933 --> 00:51:12,993
What a relief. He cleared it all up.

663
00:51:15,605 --> 00:51:17,605
You believe him?

664
00:51:19,443 --> 00:51:21,443
Of course.

665
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:26,149
Isn't it that it's easier to believe him?

666
00:51:26,249 --> 00:51:28,518
But we can corroborate his story
with Mr. McGuinn.

667
00:51:28,618 --> 00:51:30,487
Mmm-hmm.

668
00:51:30,587 --> 00:51:32,587
Yes.

669
00:51:33,390 --> 00:51:36,195
These types of people are clever.

670
00:51:39,763 --> 00:51:42,732
Well, I'm convinced.
- You're not.

671
00:51:43,266 --> 00:51:48,805
You just want things to be resolved
so you can have simplicity back.

672
00:51:48,905 --> 00:51:51,008
I want no further part of this.

673
00:51:51,108 --> 00:51:52,376
(SIGHING)

674
00:51:52,476 --> 00:51:54,476
I'll bring him down.

675
00:51:55,979 --> 00:51:59,379
How can you be so sure that he is lying?

676
00:52:02,786 --> 00:52:04,786
Experience.

677
00:52:06,790 --> 00:52:08,849
You just don't like him.

678
00:52:09,593 --> 00:52:12,963
You don't like it
that he uses a ballpoint pen.

679
00:52:13,063 --> 00:52:16,566
You don't like it that he takes
three lumps of sugar in his tea.

680
00:52:16,666 --> 00:52:18,835
You don't like it
that he likes Frosty the Snowman,

681
00:52:18,935 --> 00:52:25,008
and you are letting that convince you
of something terrible, just terrible.

682
00:52:25,108 --> 00:52:27,828
Well, I like Frosty the Snowman.

683
00:52:28,345 --> 00:52:30,647
And I think it would be nice
if this school weren't run like a jail,

684
00:52:30,747 --> 00:52:33,050
and I think it's a good thing
that I love to teach history...

685
00:52:33,150 --> 00:52:35,252
...and that I might inspire my students
to love it, too.

686
00:52:35,352 --> 00:52:38,355
And if you judge that to mean
that I am not fit to be a teacher,

687
00:52:38,455 --> 00:52:40,455
then so be it.

688
00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:45,660
Sit down.

689
00:52:50,467 --> 00:52:52,467
(LIGHT BULB BLOWS OUT)

690
00:52:54,604 --> 00:52:57,801
Look at that. You blew out my light.

691
00:53:01,478 --> 00:53:06,716
In ancient Sparta, important matters
were decided by who shouted loudest.

692
00:53:06,816 --> 00:53:10,301
Fortunately,
we are not in ancient Sparta.

693
00:53:16,126 --> 00:53:18,061
You honestly find the students
in this school...

694
00:53:18,161 --> 00:53:21,927
...to be treated like inmates in a prison?

695
00:53:23,066 --> 00:53:24,868
No.

696
00:53:24,968 --> 00:53:31,768
Actually, they all seem fairly happy,
but they're all uniformly terrified of you.

697
00:53:31,841 --> 00:53:34,810
Yes. That's how it works.

698
00:53:36,413 --> 00:53:38,413
Sit there.

699
00:53:41,017 --> 00:53:43,076
(DIALING)...

700
00:53:44,521 --> 00:53:46,521
...(SIGHING)

701
00:53:53,697 --> 00:53:55,632
Hello, this is Sister Aloysius Beauvier,

702
00:53:55,732 --> 00:54:00,237
principal at St. Nicholas School.
Is this Mrs. Miller?

703
00:54:01,504 --> 00:54:04,479
I'm calling about your son, Donald.

704
00:54:07,844 --> 00:54:09,844
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

705
00:54:18,088 --> 00:54:22,826
FLYNN: A woman was gossiping with
a friend about a man she hardly knew.

706
00:54:22,926 --> 00:54:24,528
I know none of you have ever done this.

707
00:54:24,628 --> 00:54:26,496
(CONGREGATION CHUCKLING)

708
00:54:26,596 --> 00:54:28,891
That night she had a dream.

709
00:54:29,466 --> 00:54:34,056
A great hand appeared over her
and pointed down at her.

710
00:54:35,405 --> 00:54:40,510
She was immediately seized
with an overwhelming sense of guilt.

711
00:54:40,610 --> 00:54:43,180
The next day she went to confession.

712
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:47,190
She got the old parish priest,
Father O'Rourke.

713
00:54:47,417 --> 00:54:49,882
She told him the whole thing.

714
00:54:50,253 --> 00:54:53,916
'Is gossiping a sin?'
she asked the old man.

715
00:54:55,125 --> 00:54:59,229
'Was that the hand of God Almighty
pointing a finger at me?

716
00:54:59,329 --> 00:55:01,998
'Should I be
asking your absolution, Father?

717
00:55:02,098 --> 00:55:05,328
'Tell me,
have I done something wrong?'

718
00:55:05,935 --> 00:55:09,472
(IMITA TIN G IRISH ACCEN T)
'Yes.' Father O'Rourke answered her.

719
00:55:09,572 --> 00:55:13,531
'Yes, you ignorant,
badly brought up female.

720
00:55:14,644 --> 00:55:17,514
'You have borne false witness
against your neighbour.

721
00:55:17,614 --> 00:55:20,517
'You have played fast and loose
with his reputation,

722
00:55:20,617 --> 00:55:23,762
'and you should be heartily ashamed.'

723
00:55:24,988 --> 00:55:29,833
So the woman said she was sorry
and asked for forgiveness.

724
00:55:30,760 --> 00:55:33,593
'Not so fast,' says O'Rourke.

725
00:55:34,364 --> 00:55:38,926
'I want you to go home.
Take a pillow up on your roof,

726
00:55:39,035 --> 00:55:43,200
'cut it open with a knife,
and return here to me.'

727
00:55:44,874 --> 00:55:48,778
So the woman went home,
took a pillow off her bed,

728
00:55:48,878 --> 00:55:50,413
a knife from the drawer,

729
00:55:50,513 --> 00:55:54,551
went up the fire escape to her roof
and stabbed the pillow.

730
00:55:54,651 --> 00:55:58,088
Then she went back
to the old parish priest as instructed.

731
00:55:58,188 --> 00:56:02,249
'Did you gut the pillow with a knife?'
he says.

732
00:56:02,359 --> 00:56:05,844
'Yes, Father.' 'And what was the result?'

733
00:56:07,330 --> 00:56:09,798
'Feathers,' she said.

734
00:56:13,837 --> 00:56:15,930
'Feathers,' he repeated.

735
00:56:19,242 --> 00:56:21,792
'Feathers everywhere, Father.'

736
00:56:24,514 --> 00:56:27,483
'Now, I want you to go back...

737
00:56:27,584 --> 00:56:32,389
'and gather up every last feather
that flew out on the wind.'

738
00:56:32,489 --> 00:56:36,516
'Well, ' she said, 'it can't be done.

739
00:56:37,627 --> 00:56:42,642
'I don't know where they went.
The wind took them all over.'

740
00:56:43,333 --> 00:56:47,702
'And that,' said Father O'Rourke,
'is gossip.'

741
00:56:50,340 --> 00:56:55,355
In the name of the Father, the Son
and the Holy Ghost. Amen.

742
00:56:58,748 --> 00:57:00,748
Please rise.

743
00:57:23,606 --> 00:57:25,606
(CROW CAWING)

744
00:57:32,348 --> 00:57:35,323
What's that bird complaining about?

745
00:57:37,287 --> 00:57:39,497
What kind of bird is that?

746
00:57:39,556 --> 00:57:42,423
That a starling? A grackle?

747
00:57:45,428 --> 00:57:48,226
A crow.
- Course it is.

748
00:57:49,699 --> 00:57:51,835
Are you praying?
I didn't mean to interrupt.

749
00:57:51,935 --> 00:57:53,935
I'm not praying. No.

750
00:57:55,772 --> 00:57:57,772
You seem subdued.

751
00:57:58,775 --> 00:58:01,539
Oh, I can't sleep.

752
00:58:02,779 --> 00:58:04,779
Why not?

753
00:58:05,949 --> 00:58:07,751
Bad dreams.

754
00:58:07,851 --> 00:58:10,571
Yeah, I can't sleep on occasion.

755
00:58:11,354 --> 00:58:15,325
Why? Do you see that big hand
pointing a finger at you?

756
00:58:15,425 --> 00:58:17,425
Yes. Sometimes.

757
00:58:20,330 --> 00:58:24,410
Was your sermon
directed at anyone in particular?

758
00:58:24,868 --> 00:58:26,868
What do you think?

759
00:58:38,481 --> 00:58:42,918
I received a letter
from my brother in Maryland.

760
00:58:43,953 --> 00:58:45,953
He's very sick.

761
00:58:47,457 --> 00:58:49,793
Then maybe you should go and see him.

762
00:58:49,893 --> 00:58:51,918
I can't leave my class.

763
00:59:00,870 --> 00:59:02,870
Is it true?

764
00:59:04,507 --> 00:59:06,507
What?

765
00:59:07,210 --> 00:59:09,335
You know what I'm asking.

766
00:59:11,514 --> 00:59:13,514
No.

767
00:59:15,752 --> 00:59:20,257
I saw you put an undershirt
in Donald Miller's locker.

768
00:59:21,758 --> 00:59:26,663
He left it in the sacristy.
- Why didn't you hand it to him?

769
00:59:26,763 --> 00:59:28,763
(SIGHS)

770
00:59:29,365 --> 00:59:33,190
I'm trying to spare him
further embarrassment.

771
00:59:48,318 --> 00:59:52,058
It's me that cares about that child,
not her.

772
00:59:52,889 --> 00:59:55,609
Has she ever reached out a hand?

773
00:59:57,293 --> 01:00:01,130
That black boy needs help
or he's not gonna make it.

774
01:00:01,230 --> 01:00:03,032
If she has her way,
he'll be left to his own undoing.

775
01:00:03,132 --> 01:00:07,467
Why do you think he drank the wine?
He's in trouble.

776
01:00:09,939 --> 01:00:12,175
And she sees me talk
in a human way to these kids...

777
01:00:12,275 --> 01:00:17,146
...and she immediately assumes that
there must be something wrong with it.

778
01:00:17,246 --> 01:00:20,550
Well, I'm not gonna let her
keep this parish in the Dark Ages,

779
01:00:20,650 --> 01:00:24,187
and I'm not gonna let her
destroy my spirit of compassion.

780
01:00:24,287 --> 01:00:25,822
I'm sure that's not her intent.

781
01:00:25,922 --> 01:00:29,692
That I care about this congregation.
- I know you do.

782
01:00:29,792 --> 01:00:34,552
Like you care about your class.
You love them, don't you?

783
01:00:35,999 --> 01:00:38,124
Yes.
- And that's natural.

784
01:00:38,835 --> 01:00:42,065
How else would you relate to children?

785
01:00:44,440 --> 01:00:48,411
Now, I can look at your face
and know your philosophy.

786
01:00:48,511 --> 01:00:50,511
It's kindness.

787
01:00:51,014 --> 01:00:54,006
I don't know. I mean, of course.

788
01:00:56,285 --> 01:01:00,456
There are people
who go after your humanity, Sister,

789
01:01:00,556 --> 01:01:02,959
that tell you that
the light in your heart is a weakness.

790
01:01:03,059 --> 01:01:05,059
Don't believe it.

791
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:12,234
It's an old tactic of cruel people
to kill kindness in the name of virtue.

792
01:01:13,403 --> 01:01:16,123
There's nothing wrong with love.

793
01:01:18,574 --> 01:01:20,574
Love?

794
01:01:21,678 --> 01:01:24,781
Have you forgotten the message
of our Saviour?

795
01:01:24,881 --> 01:01:28,112
It's love of people.

796
01:01:37,527 --> 01:01:41,267
I just feel as if everything is upside down.

797
01:01:44,067 --> 01:01:45,568
(SIGHS)

798
01:01:45,668 --> 01:01:50,598
There are just times in life
when we feel lost. It happens.

799
01:01:52,675 --> 01:01:54,675
And it's a bond.

800
01:01:59,615 --> 01:02:01,615
Flowers.
- Yeah.

801
01:02:01,951 --> 01:02:03,976
To remind me of spring.

802
01:02:13,429 --> 01:02:15,429
I should be going.

803
01:02:16,299 --> 01:02:18,299
(JAMES SNIFFLING)

804
01:02:18,301 --> 01:02:20,766
I'm sorry your brother's ill.

805
01:02:22,438 --> 01:02:24,438
Thank you, Father.

806
01:02:30,246 --> 01:02:32,246
I don't believe it.

807
01:02:34,117 --> 01:02:36,117
You don't?

808
01:02:37,720 --> 01:02:39,720
No.

809
01:02:40,323 --> 01:02:43,553
Thank you, Sister.
Thank you very much.

810
01:02:53,603 --> 01:02:54,470
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

811
01:02:54,570 --> 01:02:56,139
BOY 1: Hey, Anthony.
BOY 2: That's not funny.

812
01:02:56,239 --> 01:02:58,641
BOY 3: That's also the day
that I tripped. I broke my ankle.

813
01:02:58,741 --> 01:02:59,842
GIRL: I barely...

814
01:02:59,942 --> 01:03:03,212
Father. I think I've just gotta tell somebody.

815
01:03:03,312 --> 01:03:05,692
Hello, Noreen.
- I'm in love.

816
01:03:06,582 --> 01:03:08,685
That's wonderful. Who's the lucky boy?

817
01:03:08,785 --> 01:03:11,590
Jimmy Hurley.
- Have you told him?

818
01:03:11,754 --> 01:03:13,556
BOY: For life and death,
I'd go for waffles.

819
01:03:13,656 --> 01:03:15,656
Maybe you should.

820
01:03:16,359 --> 01:03:17,860
Maybe I will, Father.

821
01:03:17,960 --> 01:03:19,362
(FLYNN CHUCKLES)

822
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:21,462
NOREEN: Jimmy.

823
01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:23,464
Jimmy Hurley?

824
01:03:24,634 --> 01:03:26,634
Come over here.

825
01:03:29,172 --> 01:03:31,212
BOY: Hurry up, already.

826
01:03:31,274 --> 01:03:33,274
Father Sherman.

827
01:03:34,377 --> 01:03:38,287
NOREEN: Jimmy,
I just gotta tell you something.

828
01:03:42,819 --> 01:03:44,020
WILLIAM: You dropped something.

829
01:03:44,120 --> 01:03:45,154
(STUDENTS LAUGHING)

830
01:03:45,254 --> 01:03:46,422
GIRL: It's not funny.

831
01:03:46,522 --> 01:03:48,647
BOY: Get out of the way.

832
01:04:01,904 --> 01:04:03,904
It's all right.

833
01:04:04,507 --> 01:04:08,842
GIRL 1: He doesn't like me.
GIRL 2: That is so easy.

834
01:04:11,147 --> 01:04:15,057
GIRL 3: My parents are gonna be
so angry at me.

835
01:04:20,323 --> 01:04:21,557
(CHILDREN LAUGHIN G)

836
01:04:21,657 --> 01:04:24,387
JAMES: Okay. Be quiet.

837
01:04:27,496 --> 01:04:29,496
I said be quiet.

838
01:04:31,167 --> 01:04:34,771
The next one of you that speaks out
of turn gets sent right to the principal.

839
01:04:34,871 --> 01:04:36,871
Now the question was,

840
01:04:37,506 --> 01:04:40,821
what was Patrick Henry's famous remark?

841
01:04:44,547 --> 01:04:46,547
Donald.
- Sister?

842
01:04:51,687 --> 01:04:53,422
What was the question?

843
01:04:53,522 --> 01:04:54,824
(BOY WHISPERS ANSWER)

844
01:04:54,924 --> 01:04:58,494
Nobody help him.
Jimmy, put your hand down.

845
01:04:58,794 --> 01:05:00,853
Donald Miller, stand up.

846
01:05:06,302 --> 01:05:10,807
What was the question, Donald?
- I don't know, Sister.

847
01:05:11,440 --> 01:05:14,075
It means you weren't listening.

848
01:05:14,277 --> 01:05:16,277
Yes, Sister.

849
01:05:16,479 --> 01:05:21,239
The question was, what was
Patrick Henry's famous remark?

850
01:05:24,387 --> 01:05:25,822
I don't know.

851
01:05:25,922 --> 01:05:27,323
'Give me liberty or give me death.'

852
01:05:27,423 --> 01:05:30,193
James Hurley,
down to the principal's office.

853
01:05:30,293 --> 01:05:32,293
Now.

854
01:05:42,468 --> 01:05:44,468
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)...

855
01:05:50,343 --> 01:05:52,343
...(SIGHING)...

856
01:05:55,648 --> 01:05:57,775
Mrs. Miller?
- Yes.

857
01:05:57,917 --> 01:05:59,917
Come in.

858
01:06:01,154 --> 01:06:03,154
Please, have a seat.

859
01:06:07,093 --> 01:06:09,584
I was changing a bulb.

860
01:06:10,329 --> 01:06:13,199
Thought I mighta had the wrong day.
You didn't answer.

861
01:06:13,299 --> 01:06:14,267
Huh?

862
01:06:14,367 --> 01:06:17,666
Oh, well, just between us,

863
01:06:19,138 --> 01:06:22,909
I was listening to a transistor radio
with an earpiece.

864
01:06:23,009 --> 01:06:25,244
Look how tiny they're making them.

865
01:06:25,344 --> 01:06:27,413
I confiscated it from one of the students,

866
01:06:27,513 --> 01:06:30,049
now I can't stop listening to it.

867
01:06:30,149 --> 01:06:32,149
You like music?

868
01:06:33,886 --> 01:06:36,013
No. News reports.

869
01:06:36,622 --> 01:06:39,092
Years ago I used to listen
to all the news reports,

870
01:06:39,192 --> 01:06:42,295
because my husband was in Italy,
in the war.

871
01:06:42,395 --> 01:06:45,262
You were a married woman?
- Yes.

872
01:06:46,232 --> 01:06:48,257
But then he was killed.

873
01:06:49,702 --> 01:06:50,937
Is your husband coming?

874
01:06:51,037 --> 01:06:53,706
Couldn't get off work.
I only have half an hour myself.

875
01:06:53,806 --> 01:06:55,108
I see. Of course. It was a lot to ask.

876
01:06:55,208 --> 01:06:58,438
I see. Of course. It was a lot to ask.

877
01:07:06,252 --> 01:07:08,252
How's Donald doing?

878
01:07:08,921 --> 01:07:12,158
He's passing his subjects.
He has average grades.

879
01:07:12,258 --> 01:07:14,692
Oh. Good.

880
01:07:15,428 --> 01:07:17,997
He was upset about getting taken off
the altar boys.

881
01:07:18,097 --> 01:07:20,327
Mmm. Did he explain why?

882
01:07:20,433 --> 01:07:23,302
He said he was caught drinking altar wine.

883
01:07:23,402 --> 01:07:25,402
That is the reason.

884
01:07:25,771 --> 01:07:28,467
Well, that seems fair.

885
01:07:30,009 --> 01:07:31,844
But he's a good boy, Sister.
He fell down there,

886
01:07:31,944 --> 01:07:34,647
but he's a good boy
pretty much down the line.

887
01:07:34,747 --> 01:07:36,747
How is he at home?

888
01:07:38,351 --> 01:07:40,653
His father beat the hell out of him
over that wine.

889
01:07:40,753 --> 01:07:42,155
Oh, he shouldn't do that.

890
01:07:42,255 --> 01:07:46,826
You don't tell my husband what to do.
You just stand back.

891
01:07:46,926 --> 01:07:50,329
My husband didn't want Donald
to come here.

892
01:07:50,429 --> 01:07:52,165
Why?
- He thought he'd have trouble...

893
01:07:52,265 --> 01:07:55,535
...with the other boys,
but that hasn't really happened.

894
01:07:55,635 --> 01:07:57,170
Good.

895
01:07:57,270 --> 01:08:01,690
That priest, Father Flynn,
been watching out for him.

896
01:08:03,142 --> 01:08:04,310
Yes.

897
01:08:04,410 --> 01:08:06,410
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

898
01:08:11,584 --> 01:08:13,584
Excuse me.

899
01:08:22,128 --> 01:08:24,163
James Hurley,
what are you doing out of class?

900
01:08:24,263 --> 01:08:26,299
Sister James sent me down.
- What for?

901
01:08:26,399 --> 01:08:29,714
Talking.
- Well, go back up and shut up.

902
01:08:30,603 --> 01:08:32,603
Go. Go.

903
01:08:36,309 --> 01:08:38,309
What's going on?

904
01:08:42,815 --> 01:08:47,065
None of your business.
Now go on. Go back to class.

905
01:08:47,153 --> 01:08:48,588
Bullshit.

906
01:08:48,688 --> 01:08:50,815
What'd you say?
- Nothing.

907
01:08:57,663 --> 01:09:00,128
You have 20 minutes, you say?

908
01:09:00,466 --> 01:09:03,236
It's just that I have to walk to work.

909
01:09:03,336 --> 01:09:05,736
Where is work?
- Parkchester.

910
01:09:05,838 --> 01:09:09,208
If I don't start cleaning by noon,
I'm not home to let Donald in.

911
01:09:09,308 --> 01:09:12,471
May I walk with you?
- I don't mind.

912
01:09:15,614 --> 01:09:17,909
JAMES: Eight sixty-fourths.

913
01:09:18,517 --> 01:09:21,721
Who can tell me
what the common denominator is?

914
01:09:21,821 --> 01:09:23,821
Nobody?

915
01:09:25,024 --> 01:09:27,254
Back already, Mr. Hurley?

916
01:09:27,960 --> 01:09:31,864
I said, back already, Mr. Hurley?
- Leave me alone.

917
01:09:31,964 --> 01:09:34,233
Who do you think you're talking to?

918
01:09:34,333 --> 01:09:38,413
This is my classroom, boy.
Don't you forget that.

919
01:09:42,141 --> 01:09:44,141
I'm sorry.

920
01:09:48,948 --> 01:09:49,949
(JIMMY SNIFFLING)

921
01:09:50,049 --> 01:09:52,711
I'm sorry, Jimmy.

922
01:09:56,555 --> 01:09:58,824
ALO YSIUS: Have you met Father Flynn?

923
01:09:58,924 --> 01:10:01,294
Just seen him on the altar.
Haven't met him face to face.

924
01:10:01,394 --> 01:10:03,829
No, just, you know, heard from Donald.

925
01:10:03,929 --> 01:10:05,298
And what does he say?

926
01:10:05,398 --> 01:10:08,067
You know,
'Father Flynn, Father Flynn.'

927
01:10:08,167 --> 01:10:10,903
He looks up to him. Man gives him
his time, which is what the boy needs.

928
01:10:11,003 --> 01:10:13,003
He needs that.

929
01:10:13,038 --> 01:10:16,013
Mrs. Miller, we may have a problem.

930
01:10:17,076 --> 01:10:18,978
I thought there must a been a reason
you wanting to see me.

931
01:10:19,078 --> 01:10:21,078
Principal's a big job.

932
01:10:21,881 --> 01:10:25,117
I just want to say though,
it's just till June.

933
01:10:25,217 --> 01:10:27,217
Excuse me?

934
01:10:28,421 --> 01:10:32,191
Whatever the problem is,
Donald just has to make it till June.

935
01:10:32,291 --> 01:10:34,660
Then he's off into high school.

936
01:10:34,760 --> 01:10:36,495
Right.

937
01:10:36,595 --> 01:10:38,464
If Donald can graduate from St. Nicholas,

938
01:10:38,564 --> 01:10:41,334
he has a better chance
of getting into a good high school,

939
01:10:41,434 --> 01:10:45,259
and that would mean
an opportunity at college.

940
01:10:45,571 --> 01:10:47,306
I don't see anything at this time...

941
01:10:47,406 --> 01:10:51,877
...standing in the way
of his graduating with his class.

942
01:10:51,977 --> 01:10:55,614
Well, that's all I care about.
- I doubt that.

943
01:10:55,714 --> 01:10:57,714
Try me.

944
01:10:59,752 --> 01:11:04,557
I am concerned about the relationship
between Father Flynn and your son.

945
01:11:04,657 --> 01:11:08,294
You don't say. Concerned.
What do you mean, concerned?

946
01:11:08,394 --> 01:11:10,519
That it may not be right.

947
01:11:12,064 --> 01:11:13,666
Well, there's something wrong
with everybody,

948
01:11:13,766 --> 01:11:17,536
and their soul gotta be forgiven.
I work right there.

949
01:11:17,636 --> 01:11:20,571
I am concerned, to be frank,

950
01:11:23,943 --> 01:11:28,363
that Father Flynn may have made
advances on your son.

951
01:11:32,017 --> 01:11:34,017
May have made?

952
01:11:34,420 --> 01:11:36,155
I can't be certain.

953
01:11:36,255 --> 01:11:38,255
No evidence?
- No.

954
01:11:39,191 --> 01:11:41,996
Then maybe there's nothing to it.

955
01:11:49,201 --> 01:11:52,006
I think there is something to it.

956
01:11:52,438 --> 01:11:55,107
I think Father Flynn
gave Donald that altar wine.

957
01:11:55,207 --> 01:11:57,207
Why would he do that?

958
01:11:57,443 --> 01:11:59,443
(SIGHS)...

959
01:12:00,446 --> 01:12:03,676
Has Donald been acting strangely?
- No.

960
01:12:03,782 --> 01:12:06,218
Nothing out of the ordinary?
- He's been himself.

961
01:12:06,318 --> 01:12:09,054
All right.
- Look, Sister, I don't want any trouble.

962
01:12:09,154 --> 01:12:11,424
I don't... I'm not sure
you completely understand.

963
01:12:11,524 --> 01:12:13,459
I think I understand
the kind of thing you're talking about,

964
01:12:13,559 --> 01:12:16,279
but I don't want to get into it.

965
01:12:16,295 --> 01:12:18,295
What's that?

966
01:12:20,065 --> 01:12:22,768
Look, I only have a few minutes.
Not to be disagreeing,

967
01:12:22,868 --> 01:12:25,704
but if we're talking about
something floating around...

968
01:12:25,804 --> 01:12:28,207
...between this priest and my son,
it ain't my son's fault.

969
01:12:28,307 --> 01:12:30,876
I'm not suggesting that...
- He's just a boy.

970
01:12:30,976 --> 01:12:32,211
I know.
- Twelve years old.

971
01:12:32,311 --> 01:12:33,913
If someone should be taking blame,
it should be the man...

972
01:12:34,013 --> 01:12:36,048
I know. I agree with you completely.
...not the boy.

973
01:12:36,148 --> 01:12:37,416
You're agreeing with me,
but I got called...

974
01:12:37,516 --> 01:12:38,651
...to the principal,
if you know what I'm saying.

975
01:12:38,751 --> 01:12:42,152
I am concerned about Donald's welfare.

976
01:12:44,323 --> 01:12:46,425
You honestly think that priest
gave Donald that wine to drink?

977
01:12:46,525 --> 01:12:47,893
Yes, I do.

978
01:12:47,993 --> 01:12:50,396
Then how come my son
got kicked off the altar boys...

979
01:12:50,496 --> 01:12:52,565
...if it was a man that gave it to him?
- I know.

980
01:12:52,665 --> 01:12:55,640
The boy got caught, the man didn't.

981
01:12:57,903 --> 01:12:59,305
So you're giving my son the blame.
- No.

982
01:12:59,405 --> 01:13:00,406
No problem my son getting blamed,

983
01:13:00,506 --> 01:13:02,408
and you know why that is.
- Perhaps you should let me talk.

984
01:13:02,508 --> 01:13:04,610
I think you're getting upset.
- Sister, you ain't going against...

985
01:13:04,710 --> 01:13:06,045
...no man in a robe and win.
He's got the position.

986
01:13:06,145 --> 01:13:10,055
And he's got your son.
- Let him have him then.

987
01:13:11,717 --> 01:13:13,717
What?

988
01:13:15,087 --> 01:13:17,087
It's just till June.

989
01:13:19,158 --> 01:13:21,793
Do you know what you're saying?

990
01:13:22,561 --> 01:13:24,941
Know more about it than you.

991
01:13:26,665 --> 01:13:30,066
I believe this man is creating,

992
01:13:30,202 --> 01:13:32,304
or may have already brought about,

993
01:13:32,404 --> 01:13:34,840
an improper relationship with your son.

994
01:13:34,940 --> 01:13:36,742
I don't know.

995
01:13:36,842 --> 01:13:38,310
I know I am right.

996
01:13:38,410 --> 01:13:43,516
Why you gotta know something
like that for sure when you don't?

997
01:13:43,616 --> 01:13:45,996
What kind of mother are you?

998
01:13:49,622 --> 01:13:52,625
Excuse me, but you don't know enough
about life to say a thing like that, Sister.

999
01:13:52,725 --> 01:13:53,792
I know enough.

1000
01:13:53,892 --> 01:13:55,794
You know the rules maybe,
but that don't cover it.

1001
01:13:55,894 --> 01:13:57,763
I know what I won't accept.

1002
01:13:57,863 --> 01:13:59,965
You accept what you gotta accept,
and you work with it.

1003
01:14:00,065 --> 01:14:01,166
This man is in my school.

1004
01:14:01,266 --> 01:14:02,368
Well, he's gotta be somewhere and...

1005
01:14:02,468 --> 01:14:04,136
...maybe he's doing some good, too.
- He is after the boys.

1006
01:14:04,236 --> 01:14:08,316
Well, maybe some of them boys
want to get caught.

1007
01:14:19,585 --> 01:14:22,220
That's why his father beat him.

1008
01:14:25,624 --> 01:14:27,624
Not the wine.

1009
01:14:35,401 --> 01:14:37,441
What are you telling me?

1010
01:14:41,774 --> 01:14:45,089
I'm talking about the boy's nature now,

1011
01:14:45,978 --> 01:14:47,978
not anything he's done.

1012
01:14:49,782 --> 01:14:55,052
You can't hold a child responsible
for what God gave him to be.

1013
01:14:56,488 --> 01:14:59,558
I'm only interested in actions,
Mrs. Miller.

1014
01:14:59,658 --> 01:15:01,560
But then there's the boy's nature.

1015
01:15:01,660 --> 01:15:05,400
Leave that out of it.
- Well, forget it then.

1016
01:15:06,198 --> 01:15:09,938
You're the one forcing people to say things.

1017
01:15:12,838 --> 01:15:14,039
My boy came to your school...

1018
01:15:14,139 --> 01:15:18,559
'cause they were gonna kill him
in the public school.

1019
01:15:20,345 --> 01:15:22,555
His father don't like him.

1020
01:15:23,048 --> 01:15:26,703
He come to your school,
kids don't like him.

1021
01:15:26,852 --> 01:15:29,912
One man is good to him, this priest.

1022
01:15:30,389 --> 01:15:33,619
Then does a man have his reasons, yes.

1023
01:15:34,326 --> 01:15:37,471
Everybody does.
You have your reasons,

1024
01:15:38,697 --> 01:15:42,437
but do I ask the man
why he's good to my son?

1025
01:15:43,802 --> 01:15:45,802
No.

1026
01:15:48,741 --> 01:15:50,741
I don't care why.

1027
01:15:53,979 --> 01:15:58,712
My son needs some man
to care about him...

1028
01:16:00,018 --> 01:16:03,555
...and to see him through
to where he wants to go.

1029
01:16:03,655 --> 01:16:05,557
And thank God this educated man...

1030
01:16:05,657 --> 01:16:08,627
...with some kindness in him
wants to do just that.

1031
01:16:08,727 --> 01:16:11,430
This will not do.
- It's just till June.

1032
01:16:11,530 --> 01:16:13,565
I'll throw your son out of this school.

1033
01:16:13,665 --> 01:16:15,834
And why would you do that
if it didn't start with him?

1034
01:16:15,934 --> 01:16:18,232
Because I will stop this.

1035
01:16:18,370 --> 01:16:20,139
You'd hurt my son to get your way?

1036
01:16:20,239 --> 01:16:23,142
It won't end with your son.
- Throw the priest out then.

1037
01:16:23,242 --> 01:16:28,342
I am trying to do just that.
- Then what do you want from me?

1038
01:16:35,053 --> 01:16:37,053
Nothing.

1039
01:16:37,890 --> 01:16:39,890
(SIGHING)

1040
01:16:40,692 --> 01:16:42,692
As it turns out.

1041
01:16:43,462 --> 01:16:46,947
(CRYING) Please leave my son out of this.

1042
01:16:54,373 --> 01:16:58,963
My husband will kill that child
over a thing like this.

1043
01:17:07,653 --> 01:17:09,653
I will try.

1044
01:17:19,097 --> 01:17:21,097
I'm late.

1045
01:17:23,168 --> 01:17:25,168
Sister,

1046
01:17:27,306 --> 01:17:30,961
I don't know if you and me
on the same side.

1047
01:17:31,310 --> 01:17:35,848
I'll be standing with my son
and those who are good with my son.

1048
01:17:35,948 --> 01:17:39,603
It'd be nice to see you there.
Good morning.

1049
01:18:58,497 --> 01:19:00,497
May I come in?

1050
01:19:00,732 --> 01:19:02,434
A third party would be required.

1051
01:19:02,534 --> 01:19:06,019
Yeah. What was Donald's mother
doing here?

1052
01:19:06,171 --> 01:19:08,674
We were having a chat.
- About what?

1053
01:19:08,774 --> 01:19:10,275
A third party
would truly be required, Father.

1054
01:19:10,375 --> 01:19:12,144
No, Sister. No third party.

1055
01:19:12,244 --> 01:19:14,906
Me and you are due for a talk.

1056
01:19:15,047 --> 01:19:17,516
You have to stop this campaign against me.

1057
01:19:17,616 --> 01:19:20,517
You can stop it at any time.
- How?

1058
01:19:20,619 --> 01:19:21,787
Confess and resign.

1059
01:19:21,887 --> 01:19:24,189
You are attempting
to destroy my reputation.

1060
01:19:24,289 --> 01:19:27,520
Who keeps opening my window?

1061
01:19:29,094 --> 01:19:30,963
What are you doing in this school?

1062
01:19:31,063 --> 01:19:33,063
I'm trying to do good.

1063
01:19:33,432 --> 01:19:35,525
Even more to the point,

1064
01:19:35,634 --> 01:19:38,604
what are you doing in the priesthood?

1065
01:19:38,704 --> 01:19:43,108
You are single-handedly holding
this school and this parish back.

1066
01:19:43,208 --> 01:19:45,143
From what?
- Progressive education...

1067
01:19:45,243 --> 01:19:46,445
...and a welcoming church.

1068
01:19:46,545 --> 01:19:48,680
You can't distract me, Father.

1069
01:19:48,780 --> 01:19:50,282
This is not about my behavior,
it's about yours.

1070
01:19:50,382 --> 01:19:52,384
No, this is about
your unfounded suspicions.

1071
01:19:52,484 --> 01:19:55,721
That's right. I have suspicions.
- Just leave that. It's not important.

1072
01:19:55,821 --> 01:19:57,821
I will decide...

1073
01:20:00,759 --> 01:20:02,759
...what's important.

1074
01:20:02,794 --> 01:20:06,109
Why do you suspect me?
What have I done?

1075
01:20:07,165 --> 01:20:10,903
You gave that boy wine,
and you let him take the blame.

1076
01:20:11,003 --> 01:20:13,972
That's completely untrue.
Did you talk to Mr. McGuinn?

1077
01:20:14,072 --> 01:20:16,475
All McGuinn knows
is that the boy drank wine.

1078
01:20:16,575 --> 01:20:18,744
He doesn't know how he came to drink it.

1079
01:20:18,844 --> 01:20:21,079
Did his mother
have something to add to that?

1080
01:20:21,179 --> 01:20:23,179
No.

1081
01:20:23,248 --> 01:20:26,911
So that's it.
- I am not satisfied.

1082
01:20:27,019 --> 01:20:29,019
Ask the boy then.

1083
01:20:29,354 --> 01:20:32,090
He'd protect you.
- Why would he do that?

1084
01:20:32,190 --> 01:20:36,092
Because you have seduced him.
- You're insane.

1085
01:20:36,194 --> 01:20:38,697
You've got it in your head
that I corrupted this child...

1086
01:20:38,797 --> 01:20:41,867
...after giving him wine,
and nothing I say will change that.

1087
01:20:41,967 --> 01:20:43,201
That's right.

1088
01:20:43,301 --> 01:20:44,870
But this has nothing to do with the wine.

1089
01:20:44,970 --> 01:20:48,173
Not really. You've had a fundamental
mistrust of me before this incident.

1090
01:20:48,273 --> 01:20:52,077
It was you that warned Sister James
to be on the lookout, wasn't it?

1091
01:20:52,177 --> 01:20:53,445
That's true.

1092
01:20:53,545 --> 01:20:55,925
So you admit it.
- Certainly.

1093
01:20:57,382 --> 01:20:59,382
Why?

1094
01:21:00,852 --> 01:21:02,852
I know people.

1095
01:21:03,855 --> 01:21:05,357
That's not good enough.

1096
01:21:05,457 --> 01:21:08,262
It won't have to be.
- How's that?

1097
01:21:08,360 --> 01:21:11,420
You will tell me what you have done.

1098
01:21:12,597 --> 01:21:14,597
Oh, I will.

1099
01:21:16,401 --> 01:21:18,401
Out again.

1100
01:21:19,337 --> 01:21:22,274
Sister James is convinced I'm innocent.

1101
01:21:22,374 --> 01:21:24,924
So you talked to Sister James.

1102
01:21:25,744 --> 01:21:27,980
Well, of course you talked to Sister James.

1103
01:21:28,080 --> 01:21:30,148
Did you know Donald's father beats him?

1104
01:21:30,248 --> 01:21:31,550
Yes.

1105
01:21:31,650 --> 01:21:34,653
And might that not account
for the odd behaviour

1106
01:21:34,753 --> 01:21:37,517
Sister James noticed in the boy?

1107
01:21:37,722 --> 01:21:39,224
It might.

1108
01:21:39,324 --> 01:21:41,324
Then what is it? What?

1109
01:21:42,060 --> 01:21:44,296
(STAMMERING) What did you hear?

1110
01:21:44,396 --> 01:21:48,561
What did you see
that convinced you so thoroughly?

1111
01:21:49,334 --> 01:21:51,334
What does it matter?

1112
01:21:52,070 --> 01:21:56,370
It matters. What does it matter?
I want to know.

1113
01:22:08,220 --> 01:22:10,220
Out this window,

1114
01:22:10,622 --> 01:22:15,082
I saw you grab William London's wrist,

1115
01:22:15,227 --> 01:22:19,061
and I saw him pull away.

1116
01:22:34,846 --> 01:22:36,939
Are you serious?
- I am.

1117
01:22:38,650 --> 01:22:40,650
That's all?

1118
01:22:40,819 --> 01:22:43,617
Yeah. That was all.

1119
01:22:47,325 --> 01:22:49,325
That's nothing.

1120
01:22:51,096 --> 01:22:54,266
What are you doing now?
- I'm writing down what you say.

1121
01:22:54,366 --> 01:23:00,401
It might be important when I have
to explain why you have to be removed.

1122
01:23:04,476 --> 01:23:08,013
This morning before I spoke
with Mrs. Miller,

1123
01:23:08,113 --> 01:23:12,117
I took the precaution
of calling your last parish.

1124
01:23:12,217 --> 01:23:14,217
What did he say?

1125
01:23:14,786 --> 01:23:16,786
Who?
- The pastor.

1126
01:23:18,657 --> 01:23:22,652
I did not speak to the pastor.
I spoke to a nun.

1127
01:23:23,195 --> 01:23:26,340
You should have spoken to the pastor.

1128
01:23:27,032 --> 01:23:28,300
I spoke to a nun.

1129
01:23:28,400 --> 01:23:30,869
You know that's not the proper route
for you to have taken, Sister.

1130
01:23:30,969 --> 01:23:33,872
The church is very clear. You're
supposed to go through the pastor.

1131
01:23:33,972 --> 01:23:36,875
Why? You have an understanding,
you and he?

1132
01:23:36,975 --> 01:23:39,978
No, you have no right to go rummaging
through my past.

1133
01:23:40,078 --> 01:23:41,913
You have a history.

1134
01:23:42,013 --> 01:23:44,716
This is your third parish in five years.

1135
01:23:44,816 --> 01:23:46,284
Why?
- Call the pastor.

1136
01:23:46,384 --> 01:23:49,054
Ask him why I left.
It's perfectly innocent.

1137
01:23:49,154 --> 01:23:51,957
I'm not calling the pastor.
- I'm a good priest.

1138
01:23:52,057 --> 01:23:55,127
Go after another child and
another child, until you are stopped.

1139
01:23:55,227 --> 01:23:57,729
What nun did you speak to?
- I won't say.

1140
01:23:57,829 --> 01:24:01,266
Yeah, I've not touched a child.
- You have.

1141
01:24:01,366 --> 01:24:03,735
You haven't the slightest proof of anything.

1142
01:24:03,835 --> 01:24:05,504
But I have my certainty.

1143
01:24:05,604 --> 01:24:07,739
And armed with that,
I'll go to your last parish...

1144
01:24:07,839 --> 01:24:10,842
...and the one before that.
If necessary, I'll find a parent.

1145
01:24:10,942 --> 01:24:13,577
Trust me, Father Flynn, I will.

1146
01:24:14,412 --> 01:24:17,557
You have no right to act on your own.

1147
01:24:18,216 --> 01:24:22,380
You have taken vows,
obedience being one.

1148
01:24:22,520 --> 01:24:24,322
You answer to us.

1149
01:24:24,422 --> 01:24:27,459
You have no right
to step outside the church.

1150
01:24:27,559 --> 01:24:31,129
I will step outside the church
if that's what needs to be done,

1151
01:24:31,229 --> 01:24:32,998
though the door should shut behind me.

1152
01:24:33,098 --> 01:24:38,028
I will do what needs to be done,
though I'm damned to hell.

1153
01:24:38,236 --> 01:24:42,605
You should understand that,
or you will mistake me.

1154
01:24:45,744 --> 01:24:49,569
Now, did you give Donald Miller
wine to drink?

1155
01:24:50,215 --> 01:24:53,190
Have you never done anything wrong?

1156
01:24:53,385 --> 01:24:55,615
I have.
- No mortal sin?

1157
01:25:05,230 --> 01:25:07,230
Yes.

1158
01:25:08,400 --> 01:25:10,400
And?

1159
01:25:12,304 --> 01:25:15,967
I confessed it, Father.

1160
01:25:18,743 --> 01:25:20,953
Then whatever I have done,

1161
01:25:21,513 --> 01:25:25,593
I have left in the healing hands
of my confessor.

1162
01:25:26,184 --> 01:25:28,184
As have you.

1163
01:25:29,187 --> 01:25:31,187
We are the same.

1164
01:25:35,226 --> 01:25:37,226
Mmm-mmm.

1165
01:25:38,830 --> 01:25:41,890
No, we are not. We are not the same.

1166
01:25:51,943 --> 01:25:55,088
A dog that bites is a dog that bites.

1167
01:25:57,115 --> 01:26:00,600
Did you give Donald Miller wine to drink?

1168
01:26:01,219 --> 01:26:03,219
No.

1169
01:26:03,888 --> 01:26:05,888
Mental reservations?

1170
01:26:07,025 --> 01:26:09,025
No.

1171
01:26:11,296 --> 01:26:13,296
You lie.

1172
01:26:16,234 --> 01:26:18,234
Very well then.

1173
01:26:20,372 --> 01:26:24,536
If you will not leave my office, I will.

1174
01:26:28,046 --> 01:26:30,947
And once I go, I will not stop.

1175
01:26:37,088 --> 01:26:39,088
FLYNN: Wait.

1176
01:26:57,642 --> 01:26:59,642
(ALO YSIUS SIGHS)

1177
01:27:05,016 --> 01:27:08,331
I can't say everything, you understand?

1178
01:27:09,721 --> 01:27:12,016
There's things I can't say,

1179
01:27:13,925 --> 01:27:16,895
even if you can't imagine
the explanation, Sister.

1180
01:27:16,995 --> 01:27:18,530
(SIGHING)

1181
01:27:18,630 --> 01:27:23,192
Remember, there are things
beyond your knowledge.

1182
01:27:24,936 --> 01:27:29,873
Even if you feel certainty,
it is an emotion, not a fact.

1183
01:27:34,612 --> 01:27:37,162
You will request a transfer...

1184
01:27:38,616 --> 01:27:42,781
...and take a leave of absence
until it's granted.

1185
01:27:44,656 --> 01:27:46,681
You'd leave me nothing.

1186
01:27:47,459 --> 01:27:50,434
It's Donald Miller who has nothing,

1187
01:27:51,396 --> 01:27:53,231
and you took full advantage of that.

1188
01:27:53,331 --> 01:27:57,241
I've done nothing wrong.
I care about that boy.

1189
01:27:58,303 --> 01:28:00,303
Why?

1190
01:28:03,007 --> 01:28:05,066
'Cause you smile at him?

1191
01:28:06,110 --> 01:28:08,490
And you sympathize with him?

1192
01:28:09,481 --> 01:28:13,136
And you talk to him
as if you were the same?

1193
01:28:16,020 --> 01:28:18,454
You are a cheat.

1194
01:28:21,793 --> 01:28:25,193
And that warm feeling you experienced...

1195
01:28:25,430 --> 01:28:31,635
...when that boy looked at you with trust
was not the sensation of virtue.

1196
01:28:31,936 --> 01:28:36,441
That could be got by any drunkard
with his tot of rum.

1197
01:28:37,709 --> 01:28:39,709
I can fight you.

1198
01:28:40,144 --> 01:28:42,144
You will lose.

1199
01:28:44,849 --> 01:28:46,889
Where's your compassion?

1200
01:28:49,354 --> 01:28:51,564
Nowhere you can get at it.

1201
01:28:54,893 --> 01:28:58,021
Stay here. Compose yourself.

1202
01:28:59,731 --> 01:29:02,791
You can use the phone if you'd like.

1203
01:29:03,735 --> 01:29:05,735
Good day, Father.

1204
01:29:16,848 --> 01:29:19,143
I have no sympathy for you.

1205
01:29:21,553 --> 01:29:25,208
I know you are invulnerable to true regret.

1206
01:29:31,262 --> 01:29:33,262
And cut your nails.

1207
01:30:21,479 --> 01:30:26,239
(ORGAN PLAYS PRAISE GOD, FRO M
WHO M ALL BLESSIN GS FLOW)

1208
01:30:27,919 --> 01:30:33,585
CHOIR: (SIN GIN G) Praise God,
from whom all blessings flow

1209
01:30:33,858 --> 01:30:39,023
Praise him all creatures here below

1210
01:30:39,764 --> 01:30:44,997
Praise him above, ye heavenly host

1211
01:30:45,637 --> 01:30:51,542
Praise Father, Son and Holy Ghost

1212
01:30:51,943 --> 01:30:57,882
Amen

1213
01:31:05,923 --> 01:31:08,303
I never like to say goodbye,

1214
01:31:11,529 --> 01:31:17,819
but there is a wind behind every one
of us that takes us through our lives.

1215
01:31:18,636 --> 01:31:22,572
We never see it. We can't command it.

1216
01:31:24,042 --> 01:31:26,677
We don't even know its purpose.

1217
01:31:28,880 --> 01:31:31,916
'Cause I would have stayed
among you longer,

1218
01:31:32,016 --> 01:31:34,736
but that wind is taking me away.

1219
01:31:39,891 --> 01:31:41,891
I will miss it here,

1220
01:31:43,327 --> 01:31:45,327
and I will miss you.

1221
01:31:46,998 --> 01:31:51,078
But I'm content that the power
that propels me...

1222
01:31:52,236 --> 01:31:55,381
...does so with superior knowledge...

1223
01:31:56,340 --> 01:31:58,890
...as to what is for the best,

1224
01:32:00,912 --> 01:32:02,912
and that is my faith.

1225
01:32:07,251 --> 01:32:10,588
I would like to come
down now among you...

1226
01:32:10,688 --> 01:32:12,688
...and say goodbye...

1227
01:32:13,925 --> 01:32:16,815
...and wish you peaceful hearts...

1228
01:32:16,861 --> 01:32:18,861
...and loving hearts.

1229
01:32:22,200 --> 01:32:24,200
(ORGAN PLAYING)...

1230
01:32:26,304 --> 01:32:29,574
...(CHOIR SINGING
UBI CARITAS E T AMOR IN LATIN)...

1231
01:32:29,674 --> 01:32:31,884
Goodbye, Senator.
- Father.

1232
01:32:32,577 --> 01:32:34,312
FLYNN: Carol. Thank you so much.
Thank you.

1233
01:32:34,412 --> 01:32:36,114
CAROL: Bless you, Father.

1234
01:32:36,214 --> 01:32:39,817
Happy holidays. Susan. Bless you.
- Thank you, Father.

1235
01:32:39,917 --> 01:32:42,477
Father.
- Thank you.

1236
01:32:42,587 --> 01:32:45,021
Be good. Thank you.

1237
01:32:45,123 --> 01:32:49,458
Thank you, Father.
- Thank you very much. Thank you.

1238
01:32:52,730 --> 01:32:54,770
Paul. Thank you so much.

1239
01:32:55,566 --> 01:32:58,433
God bless you. Goodbye.

1240
01:33:22,927 --> 01:33:24,927
(BELL TOLLING)...

1241
01:33:38,643 --> 01:33:41,079
...(SIN GIN G ON RADIO)... a midnight clear

1242
01:33:41,179 --> 01:33:45,047
A glorious song of old

1243
01:33:45,583 --> 01:33:50,145
From angels bending near the Earth...

1244
01:34:03,901 --> 01:34:05,901
...(SNIFFLING)

1245
01:34:14,178 --> 01:34:17,079
Sister James. Welcome back.

1246
01:34:17,181 --> 01:34:18,583
Thank you, Sister.

1247
01:34:18,683 --> 01:34:21,828
You were missed. How is your brother?

1248
01:34:21,986 --> 01:34:23,688
Better. Much better.

1249
01:34:23,788 --> 01:34:26,814
I'm very glad. I prayed for him.

1250
01:34:29,060 --> 01:34:31,329
It was good to get away.
I needed to see my family.

1251
01:34:31,429 --> 01:34:34,830
Mmm. Then I'm glad you did it.

1252
01:34:38,302 --> 01:34:40,427
And Father Flynn is gone?

1253
01:34:41,706 --> 01:34:43,706
Yes.

1254
01:34:45,877 --> 01:34:48,512
So you did it. You got him out.

1255
01:34:48,980 --> 01:34:50,980
Yes.

1256
01:34:53,050 --> 01:34:55,386
Donald Miller is heartbroken.

1257
01:34:55,486 --> 01:34:59,388
Can't be helped. It's just till June.

1258
01:35:03,494 --> 01:35:07,165
I don't think Father Flynn
did anything wrong.

1259
01:35:07,265 --> 01:35:09,460
No? He convinced you?

1260
01:35:10,101 --> 01:35:12,101
Yes, he did.
- Mmm.

1261
01:35:17,708 --> 01:35:19,708
Did you ever prove it?

1262
01:35:20,845 --> 01:35:24,372
To whom?
- Anyone but yourself?

1263
01:35:25,716 --> 01:35:27,285
Nope.

1264
01:35:27,385 --> 01:35:29,910
But you were sure?
- Yes.

1265
01:35:34,425 --> 01:35:36,720
I wish I could be like you.

1266
01:35:38,729 --> 01:35:40,729
Why?

1267
01:35:41,465 --> 01:35:44,015
Because I can't sleep anymore.

1268
01:35:47,471 --> 01:35:51,202
Maybe we're not supposed to sleep so well.

1269
01:35:53,978 --> 01:35:57,803
They made Father Flynn
pastor of Saint Jerome.

1270
01:35:59,650 --> 01:36:02,676
Who?
- The bishop.

1271
01:36:05,790 --> 01:36:11,145
Appointed Father Flynn pastor
of Saint Jerome Church and School.

1272
01:36:12,096 --> 01:36:14,096
It's a promotion.

1273
01:36:15,232 --> 01:36:16,868
You didn't tell them?

1274
01:36:16,968 --> 01:36:22,663
Oh, I told our good monsignor.
I crossed the garden, and I told him.

1275
01:36:25,343 --> 01:36:28,148
He did not believe it to be true.

1276
01:36:31,749 --> 01:36:34,411
Then why did Father Flynn go?

1277
01:36:34,518 --> 01:36:37,493
What did you say to make him leave?

1278
01:36:37,755 --> 01:36:41,665
That I had called a nun
in his previous parish,

1279
01:36:42,660 --> 01:36:47,335
that I had found out
his prior history of infringements.

1280
01:36:52,336 --> 01:36:54,336
So you did prove it?

1281
01:36:58,676 --> 01:37:00,676
I made no such call.

1282
01:37:04,682 --> 01:37:07,583
You lied?
- Yes.

1283
01:37:08,886 --> 01:37:14,071
But if he'd had no such history,
the lie wouldn't have worked.

1284
01:37:17,161 --> 01:37:20,136
His resignation was his confession.

1285
01:37:24,835 --> 01:37:27,300
He was what I thought he was.

1286
01:37:30,207 --> 01:37:32,207
And he's gone.

1287
01:37:36,647 --> 01:37:38,772
I can't believe you lied.

1288
01:37:44,555 --> 01:37:47,020
In the pursuit of wrongdoing,

1289
01:37:47,858 --> 01:37:50,349
one steps away from God.

1290
01:37:54,031 --> 01:37:56,411
Of course, there is a price.

1291
01:38:04,842 --> 01:38:06,842
I see.

1292
01:38:14,985 --> 01:38:16,487
Oh.

1293
01:38:16,587 --> 01:38:18,587
Sister James.

1294
01:38:19,523 --> 01:38:21,523
What is it, Sister?

1295
01:38:27,531 --> 01:38:29,531
I have doubts.

1296
01:38:34,105 --> 01:38:36,105
(SIGHING)

1297
01:38:36,107 --> 01:38:40,441
I have such doubts.

1298
01:38:41,879 --> 01:38:44,769
(ORGAN PLAYING THE FIRS T NOEL)...

1299
01:39:28,959 --> 01:39:35,660
...(SIN GIN G) Come, thou,
redeemer of the Earth

1300
01:39:36,033 --> 01:39:42,768
And manifest thy virgin birth

1301
01:39:43,040 --> 01:39:49,741
Let every age adoring fall

1302
01:39:49,980 --> 01:39:56,909
Such birth befits the God of all

1303
01:39:58,389 --> 01:40:05,124
Begotten of no human will

1304
01:40:05,529 --> 01:40:12,059
But of the Spirit, thou art still

1305
01:40:12,570 --> 01:40:19,533
The word of God in flesh arrayed

1306
01:40:20,010 --> 01:40:26,848
The promised fruit to man displayed

1307
01:40:28,886 --> 01:40:35,621
The virgin womb that burden gained

1308
01:40:35,859 --> 01:40:42,423
With virgin honor all unstained

1309
01:40:43,067 --> 01:40:49,700
The banners there of virtue glow

1310
01:40:50,241 --> 01:40:57,044
God in his temple dwells below

1311
01:40:59,717 --> 01:41:06,452
Forth from his chamber goeth he

1312
01:41:06,857 --> 01:41:13,695
That royal home of purity

1313
01:41:14,131 --> 01:41:21,094
A giant in twofold substance one

1314
01:41:21,572 --> 01:41:28,501
Rejoicing now his course to run

1315
01:41:30,681 --> 01:41:37,644
From God the Father he proceeds

1316
01:41:37,988 --> 01:41:44,951
To God the Father back he speeds

1317
01:41:45,529 --> 01:41:52,492
His course he runs to death and hell

1318
01:41:52,870 --> 01:41:59,833
Returning on God's throne to dwell

1319
01:42:02,313 --> 01:42:09,219
O equal to thy Father, thou

1320
01:42:09,320 --> 01:42:16,123
Gird on thy fleshly mantle now

1321
01:42:16,593 --> 01:42:23,522
The weakness of our mortal state

1322
01:42:24,068 --> 01:42:31,031
With deathless might invigorate

1323
01:42:33,677 --> 01:42:40,515
Thy cradle here shall glitter bright

1324
01:42:40,918 --> 01:42:47,847
And darkness breathe a newer light

1325
01:42:48,192 --> 01:42:55,155
Where endless faith shall shine serene

1326
01:42:55,399 --> 01:43:02,328
And twilight never intervene

1327
01:43:04,641 --> 01:43:11,604
All praise, eternal Son, to thee

1328
01:43:13,083 --> 01:43:19,022
Whose advent sets thy people free

1329
01:43:19,123 --> 01:43:25,961
Whom, with the Father, we adore

1330
01:43:26,597 --> 01:43:33,435
And Holy Ghost for evermore

1331
01:43:35,939 --> 01:43:42,902
Amen

